==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crookes tube
<hw>Crookes" tube`</hw> <pr>(kr??ks" t?b`)</pr>. <fld>(Phys.)</fld>
<def>A vacuum tube in which the exhaustion is carried to a very high
degree, with the production of a distinct class of effects; -- so called
from <person>W. <etsep>Crookes</etsep></person> who introduced
it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>crookneck</ent>⟦br⟧
